# Key Business Questions Explored:
- Which customer groups have the highest churn rate?
- How does contract type affect churn behavior?
- Are customers with certain internet services more likely to churn?
- Does premium tech support reduce churn risk?
- How does customer satisfaction relate to churn?
- At what tenure stage are customers most likely to leave?
#
# Main Insights:
- Month-to-month customers showed the highest churn risk.
- Fiber optic customers were more likely to churn than DSL or cable users.
- Customers without premium tech support were significantly more likely to churn.
- Lower satisfaction scores were strongly associated with churn.
- Many churned customers left within the first year.
#
# Business Value:
These findings can help the company identify high-risk customer segments,
improve retention strategies, and prioritize customer support initiatives.
The cleaned analysis was used to support an executive dashboard in Power BI.
